{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":8056,"text":"You might think there are\nmany things that I can't do"},{"time":11693,"text":"because I cannot see."},{"time":14326,"text":"That's largely true."},{"time":15998,"text":"Actually, I just needed\nto have a bit of help"},{"time":18505,"text":"to come up to the stage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":20363,"text":"But there is also a lot that I can do."},{"time":23730,"text":"This is me rock climbing\nfor the first time."},{"time":27166,"text":"Actually, I love sports\nand I can play many sports,"},{"time":31267,"text":"like swimming, skiing, skating,\nscuba diving, running and so on."},{"time":37382,"text":"But there is one limitation:"},{"time":40145,"text":"somebody needs to help me."},{"time":42514,"text":"I want to be independent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45741,"text":"I lost my sight at the age of 14\nin a swimming pool accident."},{"time":50989,"text":"I was an active, independent teenager,"},{"time":53637,"text":"and suddenly I became blind."},{"time":56840,"text":"The hardest thing for me\nwas losing my independence."},{"time":61600,"text":"Things that until then seemed simple\nbecame almost impossible to do alone."},{"time":67962,"text":"For example, one of my\nchallenges was textbooks."},{"time":72084,"text":"Back then, there were no\npersonal computers,"},{"time":74858,"text":"no Internet, no smartphones."},{"time":77319,"text":"So I had to ask one of my two brothers\nto read me textbooks,"},{"time":82776,"text":"and I had to create\nmy own books in Braille."},{"time":86653,"text":"Can you imagine?"},{"time":88603,"text":"Of course, my brothers\nwere not happy about it,"},{"time":91746,"text":"and later, I noticed they were not there\nwhenever I needed them."},{"time":95593,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":96618,"text":"I think they tried to stay away from me."},{"time":100434,"text":"I don't blame them."},{"time":102581,"text":"I really wanted to be freed\nfrom relying on someone."},{"time":107160,"text":"That became my strong desire\nto ignite innovation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112100,"text":"Jump ahead to the mid-1980s."},{"time":114810,"text":"I got to know cutting-edge technologies"},{"time":117580,"text":"and I thought to myself,"},{"time":119701,"text":"how come there is no computer technology"},{"time":123344,"text":"to create books in Braille?"},{"time":126288,"text":"These amazing technologies\nmust be able to also help people"},{"time":130676,"text":"with limitations like myself."},{"time":133805,"text":"That's the moment\nmy innovation journey began."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138686,"text":"I started developing\ndigital book technologies,"},{"time":142564,"text":"such as a digital Braille editor,\ndigital Braille dictionary"},{"time":147881,"text":"and a digital Braille library network."},{"time":151178,"text":"Today, every student who is visually\nimpaired can read textbooks,"},{"time":155570,"text":"by using personal computers\nand mobile devices,"},{"time":159421,"text":"in Braille or in voice."},{"time":161998,"text":"This may not surprise you,"},{"time":164158,"text":"since everyone now has digital books\nin their tablets in 2015."},{"time":169242,"text":"But Braille went digital\nmany years before digital books,"},{"time":175113,"text":"already in the late 1980s,\nalmost 30 years ago."},{"time":181242,"text":"Strong and specific needs\nof the blind people"},{"time":185065,"text":"made this opportunity to create\ndigital books way back then."},{"time":191343,"text":"And this is actually not\nthe first time this happened,"},{"time":196373,"text":"because history shows us\naccessibility ignites innovation."},{"time":203467,"text":"The telephone was invented\nwhile developing a communication tool"},{"time":207508,"text":"for hearing impaired people."},{"time":209737,"text":"Some keyboards were also invented\nto help people with disabilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216807,"text":"Now I'm going to give you\nanother example from my own life."},{"time":220688,"text":"In the '90s, people around me\nstarted talking about the Internet"},{"time":224975,"text":"and web browsing."},{"time":226895,"text":"I remember the first time\nI went on the web."},{"time":230148,"text":"I was astonished."},{"time":232352,"text":"I could access newspapers\nat any time and every day."},{"time":236810,"text":"I could even search\nfor any information by myself."},{"time":241175,"text":"I desperately wanted to help the blind\npeople have access to the Internet,"},{"time":247013,"text":"and I found ways to render the web\ninto synthesized voice,"},{"time":252343,"text":"which dramatically simplified\nthe user interface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256685,"text":"This led me to develop\nthe Home Page Reader in 1997,"},{"time":262119,"text":"first in Japanese and later,\ntranslated into 11 languages."},{"time":267784,"text":"When I developed the Home Page Reader,"},{"time":270385,"text":"I got many comments from users."},{"time":273909,"text":"One that I strongly remember said,"},{"time":277032,"text":"\"For me, the Internet\nis a small window to the world.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":283185,"text":"It was a revolutionary moment\nfor the blind."},{"time":287130,"text":"The cyber world became accessible,"},{"time":289331,"text":"and this technology that we created\nfor the blind has many uses,"},{"time":294025,"text":"way beyond what I imagined."},{"time":296539,"text":"It can help drivers listen to their emails"},{"time":300709,"text":"or it can help you listen\nto a recipe while cooking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306116,"text":"Today, I am more independent,"},{"time":308650,"text":"but it is still not enough."},{"time":311668,"text":"For example, when I approached\nthe stage just now, I needed assistance."},{"time":318412,"text":"My goal is to come up here independently."},{"time":322147,"text":"And not just here."},{"time":323991,"text":"My goal is to be able to travel\nand do things that are simple to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330638,"text":"OK, now let me show you\nthe latest technologies."},{"time":333471,"text":"This is a smartphone app\nthat we are working on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338625,"text":"(Video) Electronic voice: 51 feet\nto the door, and keep straight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345702,"text":"EV: Take the two doors to go out.\nThe door is on your right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355731,"text":"EV: Nick is approaching. Looks so happy."},{"time":357693,"text":"Chieko Asakawa: Hi, Nick!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":358922,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":359947,"text":"CA: Where are you going?\nYou look so happy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362114,"text":"Nick: Oh -- well, my paper\njust got accepted."},{"time":364251,"text":"CA: That's great! Congratulations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365922,"text":"Nick: Thanks. Wait -- how'd you know\nit was me, and that I look happy?"},{"time":369597,"text":"(Chieko and Nick laugh)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":370971,"text":"Man: Hi."},{"time":372154,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":373895,"text":"CA: Oh ... hi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375070,"text":"EV: He is not talking to you,\nbut on his phone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384434,"text":"EV: Potato chips."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393159,"text":"EV: Dark chocolate with almonds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396155,"text":"EV: You gained 5 pounds since yesterday;\ntake apple instead of chocolate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399700,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":402456,"text":"EV: Approaching."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408038,"text":"EV: You arrived."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410939,"text":"CA: Now ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412202,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":416154,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417369,"text":"So now the app navigates me"},{"time":420291,"text":"by analyzing beacon signals\nand smartphone sensors"},{"time":424331,"text":"and permits me to move around\nindoor and outdoor environments"},{"time":429491,"text":"all by myself."},{"time":431103,"text":"But the computer vision part\nthat showed who is approaching,"},{"time":435975,"text":"in which mood -- we are still\nworking on that part."},{"time":440251,"text":"And recognizing facial expressions\nis very important for me to be social."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447398,"text":"So now the fusions of technologies\nare ready to help me"},{"time":453588,"text":"see the real world."},{"time":455920,"text":"We call this cognitive assistance."},{"time":459821,"text":"It understands our surrounding world"},{"time":463164,"text":"and whispers to me in voice\nor sends a vibration to my fingers."},{"time":470088,"text":"Cognitive assistance will augment\nmissing or weakened abilities --"},{"time":476176,"text":"in other words, our five senses."},{"time":479464,"text":"This technology is only in an early stage,"},{"time":482799,"text":"but eventually, I'll be able to find\na classroom on campus,"},{"time":487600,"text":"enjoy window shopping"},{"time":489378,"text":"or find a nice restaurant\nwhile walking along a street."},{"time":494088,"text":"It will be amazing if I can find you\non the street before you notice me."},{"time":499595,"text":"It will become my best buddy, and yours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504308,"text":"So, this really is a great challenge."},{"time":508395,"text":"It is a challenge\nthat needs collaboration,"},{"time":512388,"text":"which is why we are creating\nan open community"},{"time":515314,"text":"to accelerate research activities."},{"time":519192,"text":"Just this morning, we announced\nthe open-source fundamental technologies"},{"time":524114,"text":"you just saw in the video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526487,"text":"The frontier is the real world."},{"time":529878,"text":"The blind community is exploring\nthis technical frontier"},{"time":534315,"text":"and the pathfinder."},{"time":536559,"text":"I hope to work with you\nto explore the new era,"},{"time":540321,"text":"and the next time that I'm on this stage,"},{"time":543432,"text":"through technology and innovation,"},{"time":545870,"text":"I will be able to walk up here"},{"time":547919,"text":"all by myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549539,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550802,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}